full_text:
So, perhaps one of the serendipitous things that has come out of 2020, is a deeper understanding- of myself, of God, of others. And for that, I rejoice. 
Thank you for coming to my TED Talk.
#PastorLife #MentalHealth #Depression #SelfCare #LearningToWalkInTheDark
full_text(utf-8): b'So, perhaps one of the serendipitous things that has come out of 2020, is a deeper understanding- of myself, of God, of others. And for that, I rejoice. \nThank you for coming to my TED Talk.\n#PastorLife #MentalHealth #Depression #SelfCare #LearningToWalkInTheDark'

full_text: Sometimes I run, sometimes I walk, other times, I crawl, or lay prostrate in complete stillness and exhaustion. But I believe that our pain can be redeemed. And, even as a pastor, I was skeptical of that at first. But I've begun to see it play out in my own life...
full_text(utf-8): b"Sometimes I run, sometimes I walk, other times, I crawl, or lay prostrate in complete stillness and exhaustion. But I believe that our pain can be redeemed. And, even as a pastor, I was skeptical of that at first. But I've begun to see it play out in my own life..."

full_text:
And even in the midst of the emptiness that depression feels like- I'm reminded of Mary Oliver's short poem:
"Somebody I loved once gave me a box full of darkness. In time, I realized, that this, too, was a gift."
I'm learning to walk in the dark, as it were...
full_text(utf-8): b'And even in the midst of the emptiness that depression feels like- I\'m reminded of Mary Oliver\'s short poem:\n"Somebody I loved once gave me a box full of darkness. In time, I realized, that this, too, was a gift."\nI\'m learning to walk in the dark, as it were...'

full_text: Now, don't get me wrong. I still struggle some days. I still wish it would just go sometimes. And I am by NO means suggesting that I have "prayed it away," or that my faith overcame it. No, I'm well medicated. That's helped LOADS...
full_text(utf-8): b'Now, don\'t get me wrong. I still struggle some days. I still wish it would just go sometimes. And I am by NO means suggesting that I have "prayed it away," or that my faith overcame it. No, I\'m well medicated. That\'s helped LOADS...'

full_text: Some days, I'm grateful for depression. Might sound odd, but I'm grateful for the gift of darkness in my life. It's helped me to deal with a lot of my baggage from my past, and given me a new and different perspective in my faith, and has helped me to see God in new ways...
full_text(utf-8): b"Some days, I'm grateful for depression. Might sound odd, but I'm grateful for the gift of darkness in my life. It's helped me to deal with a lot of my baggage from my past, and given me a new and different perspective in my faith, and has helped me to see God in new ways..."

I think it's time for me to open myself more fully to being present...
